    "family_info": {
        "description": "{'text': 'Apc4 is a component of the anaphase promoting complex/cyclosome (APC/C), a cell cycle-regulated E3 ubiquitin ligase that controls progression through mitosis and the G1 phase of the cell cycle. This complex acts by ubiquitination and degradation of target proteins. Apc4 consists of a beta-propeller that is split by      a long alpha-helical domain ([pfam:PF12816]) which generate an L-shaped molecule [[cite:PUB00137946]]. APC4 interacts with APC5; the N-terminal of APC1  serves to stabilise the union between APC4 and APC5, both of which lie towards the bottom-front of the APC [[cite:PUB00056269],[cite:PUB00055977],[cite:PUB00059190],[cite:PUB00137946]]. This entry represents the C-terminal half of the beta-propeller of ACP4 from animals [[cite:PUB00137946]].', 'llm': False, 'checked': False, 'updated': False}",
